## 🛣 PART 10 — Your Learning Roadmap

Use this order to properly learn everything your project uses.

### 🟢 Stage 1 — JavaScript Prerequisites (If Not Done)
- [ ] `const`, `let`, arrow functions
- [ ] Array methods: `map`, `filter`, `reduce`, `find`
- [ ] Destructuring: `const { a, b } = obj`, `const [x, y] = arr`
- [ ] Spread operator: `...arr`, `...obj`
- [ ] Optional chaining: `obj?.prop`
- [ ] Template literals: `` `Hello ${name}` ``
- [ ] `async/await` and `try/catch`
- [ ] ES Modules: `import`/`export`

### 🟡 Stage 2 — React Core
- [ ] What is a component? What is JSX?
- [ ] Props — passing data down
- [ ] `useState` — managing local state
- [ ] Conditional rendering (`? :` and `&&`)
- [ ] Rendering lists with `.map()` and `key` prop
- [ ] Event handlers (`onClick`, `onChange`)
- [ ] `useEffect` — side effects, dependency array
- [ ] Component composition (children, prop drilling)
- [ ] Lifting state up

### 🟠 Stage 3 — React Ecosystem
- [ ] React Router v6 — `Routes`, `Route`, `Link`, `useNavigate`, `useLocation`
- [ ] Forms in React — controlled inputs (`value` + `onChange`)
- [ ] Working with `localStorage`
- [ ] Environment variables (`import.meta.env`)

### 🔴 Stage 4 — Firebase
- [ ] What is Firebase / BaaS?
- [ ] Firebase Auth — `onAuthStateChanged`, `signInWithPopup`, `signOut`
- [ ] Google OAuth flow
- [ ] Firebase initialization & config

### 🟣 Stage 5 — Styling & Build Tools
- [ ] Tailwind CSS — utility classes, responsive prefixes
- [ ] Glassmorphism (`backdrop-blur`, transparency)
- [ ] Vite — what it does, `npm run dev` vs `npm run build`

### ⚫ Stage 6 — Advanced Patterns (In Your Code)
- [ ] Data-driven UI (your `StaticPage` + `staticPages` pattern)
- [ ] Derived state vs stored state
- [ ] Custom sub-components (`FieldControl`, `Toggle`)
- [ ] Weighted scoring algorithm logic
- [ ] ARIA accessibility attributes (`role="switch"`, `aria-checked`)

