> [!TIP]
> **Best next step:** Read through `BondCalculatorPage.jsx` line by line and trace how one field (e.g., `couponRate`) flows from: the data in `ratingModel.js` → the state in `useState` → the UI dropdown → the scoring algorithm → the displayed result. That single trace will teach you 80% of the patterns used in this project.

> [!NOTE]
> **What's missing from this project for production?**
> - No backend — the rating runs entirely in the browser (anyone can see/modify the logic)
> - No database — ratings are not saved
> - Firebase is configured but sign-in doesn't gate the calculator yet
> - No unit tests
> These are all natural next steps to level up the project!
